BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-fed810c11e3c56fa@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T141500Z
DTEND:20260612T151500Z
SUMMARY:YĪN YĪN
LOCATION:ONE
DESCRIPTION:Energetic genre-scrambling groove-machine\n\nDutch collective Y
 ĪN YĪN scramble global movements in a blender: psych rock\, Thai funk\
 , Japanese city pop... anything that tickles their current fancy.\nTheir o
 mnivorous spirit often unfolds in some of the most succulent grooves imagi
 nable\, with a vibrant assembly of traditional instruments\, vintage synth
 s and flavorful percussion spicing everything up. YĪN YĪN have truly p
 erfected the art of musical fusion cooking.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-22802bcddfeec424@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T161500Z
DTEND:20260612T171500Z
SUMMARY:Curtis Harding
LOCATION:ONE
DESCRIPTION:Modern soul man with deep bag\n\nWith a cool you simply can’t
  teach\, Curtis Harding instills his honed psychedelic sound with pure sou
 l\, gospel\, garage and funk.Harding has made a habit out of stepping into
  new musical situations like a wide-eyed student – only to seemlessly ab
 sorb them as if they're always part of his DNA. A true chameleon who keeps
  on shining in whatever musical context he operates – his sights perpetu
 ally set on the next time he shuffles his now extensive deck of influences
 .
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-7a51228c926ab5d9@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T181500Z
DTEND:20260612T191500Z
SUMMARY:De La Soul
LOCATION:ONE
DESCRIPTION:High rising hip-hop legends\n\nSince their landmark LP 3 High a
 nd Rising\, De La Soul has been a revolutionary force in hip-hop and music
  in general.\nThey opened the floodgates of what rap could be\, sampling e
 lements of pop\, jazz\, reggae and psychedelia\, plus using fun and flippa
 ncy as a counterbalance. The dawn of Da Inner Sound throughout the decades
  wasn’t without its tragedies\, as founding member Trugoy The Dove passe
 d away in 2023. The remaining members ran it back with 2025’s beaming Ca
 bin In The Sky: no rest for the wicked livin’ in the fulltime era.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-1a50c0a5e305bd23@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260612T203000Z
DTEND:20260612T220000Z
SUMMARY:Jack White
LOCATION:ONE
DESCRIPTION:Rock music's chief anti-hero\n\nA legendary guitar hero in days
  where that concept seems rarer and rarer\, Jack White never plays it safe
 .\nWith so many iconic rock songs under his name\, many would have settled
  the course. Yet White stubbornly keeps going against the grain as a sonic
  iconoclast\, tender of timeless songcraft and label owner of Third Man Re
 cords. Qualities steadily upheld in his own extensive solo output\, and in
  bands like The White Stripes\, The Dead Weather and The Raconteurs. And e
 veryone knows about it.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-cc2e6059c1419fff@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T120000Z
DTEND:20260613T124500Z
SUMMARY:Naïka
LOCATION:ONE
DESCRIPTION:Rising Transatlantic pop and R&B icon\n\nA child of overlapping
  different cultures\, languages and heritages\, Naïka is redefining the g
 lobal pop star with unrivalled aplomb.\nThe rising artist’s long awaited
  debut LP ECLESIA does exactly what its title promised: reconciling Naïka
 ’s Haitian\, French and American roots to create a warm-blooded\, forwar
 d thinking brand of Transatlantic pop. Having lead a nomadic young life\, 
 Naïka's music carves out a genre-blending sanctuary of her very own makin
 g.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-3ab2def4be52d953@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T134500Z
DTEND:20260613T144500Z
SUMMARY:Sef
LOCATION:ONE
DESCRIPTION:One of Dutch rap's chief voices\n\nYou can always count on Dutc
 h-Moroccan artist Sef to capture the moment urgently and sincerely.\nWith 
 his deeply impressive performances on big festival stages last summer\, an
 d a sold-out club tour still fresh in our minds\, Sef has solidified himse
 lf as one of Dutch rap’s leading lights. From his beloved hip-hop staple
  De Leven to latest LP lieve monsters – a dark but danceable tale of col
 lective despair – Yousef Gnaoui enters Best Kept Secret with a surplus o
 f stories\, stirring energy and moments that’ll stick with you.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-cf79ad2e4f4ec7ea@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T154500Z
DTEND:20260613T164500Z
SUMMARY:Hayley Williams
LOCATION:ONE
DESCRIPTION:Paramore icon & eclectic pop star\n\nFrom fronting pop punk ico
 ns Paramore to spearheading an illustrious solo career\, Hayley Williams's
  artistic walk of life is both singular and inspiring.Williams influenced 
 a whole generation of stars\, from Billie Eilish to Olivia Rodrigo – and
  the damnedest thing happened: those artists reinvigorated her work in ret
 urn. The 17 song release Ego Death At a Bachelorette Party is as multi-fac
 eted and free spirited as pop music gets – plus a rare shining example o
 f a grassroots and community-driven project on a mainstream level. This is
  why Hayley Williams is truly our favorite band.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-06d2807899cada81@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T174500Z
DTEND:20260613T184500Z
SUMMARY:Wolf Alice
LOCATION:ONE
DESCRIPTION:Resonant UK alt rock sensation\n\nBritains biggest indie rock b
 and Wolf Alice keeps unpacking and unraveling.\nTheir latest LP The Cleari
 ng luxuriates in aspects of some of rock music’s greatest – the melodi
 c genius of Fleetwood Mac\, the glam rock strut of T-Rex\, the technicolor
  exuberance of ELO. Wolf Alice have plenty of classics to call their own: 
 how many songs capture both the devastation and thrill of falling in love 
 better than “Don’t Delete The Kisses”? Best Kept Secret has felt thi
 s thrill many times before. Safe to say\, that third post-show dip in the 
 lake’s a charm.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-f9dd411a32ddbcf0@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260613T200000Z
DTEND:20260613T220000Z
SUMMARY:Nick Cave & The Bad Seeds
LOCATION:ONE
DESCRIPTION:Legendary songsmith of darkness and devotion\n\nFew artists enc
 ompass the profound breadth of human emotion quite like Nick Cave and his 
 Bad Seeds.\nMenacing\, majestic and often-times touching the divine\, they
  have one of the most acclaimed back catalogs around. Nick Cave's ability 
 to veer from blackened goth punk sermons to a tender-hearted gospel ballad
  is no longer a secret so well kept. After a thunderous show in 2022\, Nic
 k Cave and the Bad Seeds return to Hilvarenbeek with hymns of faith\, hope
  and carnage both new and old.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-d6ca843ac979522d@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260614T121500Z
DTEND:20260614T130000Z
SUMMARY:Jungle By Night
LOCATION:ONE
DESCRIPTION:Genre-crossing Afrofunk phenomenon\n\nSynergy isn't just the na
 me of a recent collaborative project Jungle By Night sunk their teeth in 
 – it is truly who they are.Jungle By Night has explored virtually every 
 musical style imaginable with thorough\, thoughtful cross-pollination. Dub
 \, krautrock\, psychedelic rock\, pop\, dance\, afrobeat\, hip-hop\, funk\
 , and electronic music all feature in the groundbreaking vocabulary of thi
 s vital collective. Few can bring all those rich influences together and m
 ake people move in ways they never deemed possible.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-a634796f9563d3f1@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260614T134500Z
DTEND:20260614T144500Z
SUMMARY:Sylvie Kreusch
LOCATION:ONE
DESCRIPTION:Belgium's cinematic pop superstar\n\nSylvie Kreusch has made wa
 ves as one of Europe's most electrifying stage performers.\nKnown for her 
 expressive lyricism\, strikingly cinematic imagery and genre-fluid sensibi
 lities\, the Belgian artist turned into a celluloid heroine on her latest 
 LP 'Comic Trip'. Her shows leave a carousel of vivid impressions\, from th
 e bigger fireworks to moments of unblemished\, affecting romance.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-81c87fae19c79b0e@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260614T154500Z
DTEND:20260614T164500Z
SUMMARY:Ethel Cain
LOCATION:ONE
DESCRIPTION:The queen of Southern gothic folk pop\n\nEthel Cain is one of p
 op music's most thrilling storytellers\, in both the mainstream and the fr
 inges.\nIn many ways\, Cain covers its familiar themes: the falling in lov
 e\, the coming of age\, the search for identity and belonging. But toss a 
 healthy portion of religious zealotry\, cannibalism and perversion into th
 e cauldron\, and you get of the most shocking and exhilarating musical arc
 s in recent memory. It all plays out like a Southern gothic novel set in 2
 1st Century America.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-d16cb4c0e50e0b91@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260614T174500Z
DTEND:20260614T184500Z
SUMMARY:Mac DeMarco
LOCATION:ONE
DESCRIPTION:Canadian slacker pop savant\n\nMac DeMarco continues to march t
 o his own easygoing beat.\nIn the vast outstretched lands of British Colum
 bia\, Mac is a man who enjoys his canoeing\, his riding of motorcycles and
  his building of water wells. And by the way\, he pens a lot of great jams
  as well. Hence his latest work\, coincidently called ‘Guitar’\, is as
  pure of heart as its creator. Though it seems like Mac is forever winging
  it\, his unmistakable wisdom and wry humor always simmer through.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:best-kept-secret-2026-cb833a353e26af4c@second-brain.local
DTSTAMP:20260611T103410Z
DTSTART:20260614T200000Z
DTEND:20260614T213000Z
SUMMARY:Gorillaz
LOCATION:ONE
DESCRIPTION:The most famous animated band on earth\n\nGorillaz is a world i
 n and of itself: vibrant\, urgent and endlessly innovative.\nAlmost three 
 decades in\, the adventures of 2D\, Murdoc Niccals\, Russel Hobbs and Nood
 le have guided us across Plastic Beaches and Cracker Islands\, and now in 
 its ninth episode\, clambering up The Mountain. Indeed\, the novelty of st
 arting an animated band became so much more for founders Damon Albarn and 
 Jamie Hewlett. Behind the celluloid\, Gorillaz has become a cross-generati
 onal\, genre-blending community of legends and current greats – as glori
 ous and vital as ever.\nDive into the world of Gorillaz and read our artic
 le.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
